ion)", "used_by": "dope-context MCP", "advantages": "Modern, single container, proven working"}}}, "critical_unknowns": ["How were dopemux-postgres-primary and dopemux-redis-primary started? (not in any compose file)", "What data do these mystery containers hold?", "Which MCP servers actively connect to them?", "Can we inspect their databases to see active usage?", "Is there another docker-compose file we haven't found?"], "consolidation_targets": {"phase_1_postgres": {"goal": "3 PostgreSQL \u2192 1 (dopemux-postgres-age only)", "safe_removals": ["dopemux-postgres (orphaned)", "conport-kg-postgres-age (DEFERRED)"], "requires_investigation": "dopemux-postgres-primary (mystery source)", "estimated_savings": "~1GB memory, 2 containers"}, "phase_2_redis": {"goal": "Redis consolidation to 2-3 instances", "keep": "dopemux-redis-leantime (PM plane isolation)", "requires_investigation": "dopemux-redis-primary (mystery source)", "target_architecture": "shared Redis + events Redis + Leantime Redis"}, "phase_3_vector": {"goal": "Milvus (3 containers) \u2192 Qdrant (1 container)", "migration_effort": "MEDIUM-HIGH", "risk": "Data migration, re-indexing time", "estimated_savings": "~1.5GB memory, 3 containers"}}, "zen_analysis_steps": {"step_1": "Evidence gathering: Find mystery container sources, inspect databases, check MCP configs", "step_2": "Dependency mapping: Which services depend on which databases (postgres-primary, redis-primary)", "step_3": "Data safety assessment: What data exists, is it needed, can we migrate/remove safely", "step_4": "Risk analysis: What breaks if we remove each container, rollback strategies", "step_5": "Execution planning: Optimal sequence, validation checkpoints, rollback procedures", "step_6": "Validation strategy: How to verify each phase succeeded, monitoring during execution", "step_7": "Final synthesis: Go/no-go decision, detailed execution runbook"}, "mcp_servers_to_check": ["ConPort MCP - which database? (likely postgres-age)", "dope-context - which vector DB? (likely Qdrant)", "claude-context - which vector DB? (likely Milvus)", "Serena - any database dependencies?", "GPT-Researcher - any database dependencies?"], "investigation_commands": {"find_compose_files": "find . -name 'docker-compose*.yml' -type f | grep -v node_modules", "inspect_postgres_primary": "docker exec dopemux-postgres-primary psql -U postgres -c '\\l'", "inspect_redis_primary": "docker exec dopemux-redis-primary redis-cli INFO", "check_mcp_connections": "grep -r DATABASE_URL docker/mcp-servers/ services/ --include='*.yml' --include='*.py'", "verify_milvus_usage": "docker ps | grep milvus && docker logs milvus-standalone --tail 50"}, "expected_total_savings": {"containers": "8 eliminated (2 PostgreSQL + 1 Redis + 3 Milvus + 2 DEFERRED)", "memory": "~2-3GB (PostgreSQL ~500MB each, Milvus stack ~1.5GB, Redis ~200MB)", "ports_freed": "5432, 9000, 9001, 19530, 9091 (if Milvus removed)", "maintenance_reduction": "Single PostgreSQL AGE, 2-3 Redis, 1 Qdrant vs current sprawl"}, "session_timestamp": "2025-10-16T07:15:00Z", "pause_safe": true, "context_preserved": true, "infrastructure_cleanup_session": {"zen_mcp_status": "\u2705 OPERATIONAL - Connected to Claude Code via stdio", "containers_removed": ["dopemux-postgres-primary (zombie from deleted unified.yml)"], "containers_formalized": ["dopemux-redis-primary (now managed by docker-compose)"], "volumes_cleaned": ["dopemux-mvp_postgres_primary_data", "dopemux_postgres_data", "dopemux_postgres_primary_data"], "storage_freed": "~1.5GB", "services_validated": ["ConPort \u2705 Redis connected", "redis-primary \u2705 healthy"], "decision_logged": "ConPort Decision #33"}, "decisions_this_session": [33, 34, 35], "files_modified": ["docker/mcp-servers/docker-compose.yml (-88 lines: removed unused services)", ".claude.json (+13 lines: Zen MCP stdio config)", "docker/mcp-servers/zen/zen-mcp-server/conf/cli_clients/ (+3 worktree configs)"], "architecture_validated": true, "proof_of_concept": "Create