.py (450 lines)", "src/dopemux/config_generator.py (350 lines)", "profiles/*.yaml (4 templates)", "docs/UI-DESIGN-RESEARCH-SYNTHESIS.md (13.5K words)"], "next_immediate_task": "Task 1.3: Config Generator - transform profile YAML to Claude config.json format", "session_start": "2025-10-10T08:30:00Z", "last_save": "2025-10-10T09:17:00Z", "conport_decisions_this_session": ["#17 (ADHD Themes)", "#19 (libtmux)", "#20 (Textual)", "#21 (Energy Layouts)", "#22 (Session Templates)", "#23 (Textual Deep Dive)", "#25 (Synthesis)", "#26 (Epic 1 Progress)"], "break_safe": true, "resume_instructions": "After restart with Zen MCP active: (1) Verify zen tools available with ListMcpResourcesTool. (2) Start zen/thinkdeep with step 1: Evidence gathering for mystery containers. (3) Run investigation commands to find postgres-primary and redis-primary sources. (4) Inspect databases to verify active usage. (5) Complete 7-step analysis before ANY infrastructure changes. (6) Log final decision in ConPort (Decision #33).", "total_lines_today": "1,530+ lines of profile system code", "next_task": "Task 1.4: CLI Commands (dopemux profile list/show/switch) - 1 hour estimated", "session_end_summary": "COMPREHENSIVE SESSION SAVE - Ready for git commit. ACCOMPLISHMENTS: (1) UI Design Research: 6 topics completed, 7 ConPort decisions logged (#17-#23, #25), 13.5K word synthesis document with 4-phase roadmap, 7 knowledge graph links created. (2) Profile Manager Epic 1: Tasks 1.1-1.3 complete (75% done), 1,530+ lines of production code across 4 modules (profile_models.py 380L, profile_parser.py 350L, profile_detector.py 450L, config_generator.py 350L), 4 validated profile templates (developer, researcher, architect, minimal). FILES READY TO COMMIT: src/dopemux/profile_models.py (Pydantic validation), src/dopemux/profile_parser.py (YAML discovery), src/dopemux/profile_detector.py (weighted scoring engine), src/dopemux/config_generator.py (config transformation), profiles/developer.yaml, profiles/researcher.yaml, profiles/architect.yaml, profiles/minimal.yaml, docs/UI-DESIGN-RESEARCH-SYNTHESIS.md (comprehensive reference), docs/PROFILE-YAML-SCHEMA.md (already exists). ALL TESTS PASSING: 4/4 profiles load successfully, detection engine scores correctly, config generator validates all MCPs. NEXT SESSION: Task 1.4 CLI Commands (1 hour to complete Epic 1 MVP).", "git_files_to_commit": ["src/dopemux/profile_models.py", "src/dopemux/profile_parser.py", "src/dopemux/profile_detector.py", "src/dopemux/config_generator.py", "profiles/developer.yaml", "profiles/researcher.yaml", "profiles/architect.yaml", "profiles/minimal.yaml", "docs/UI-DESIGN-RESEARCH-SYNTHESIS.md"], "commit_message_suggestion": "feat: Profile Manager foundation (Epic 1 Tasks 1.1-1.3)\n\n- Pydantic models with full validation (conport required, name format, time windows)\n- YAML parser with discovery and batch loading\n- Detection engine with weighted scoring (5 signals, ADHD thresholds)\n- Config generator transforms profiles to Claude config.json\n- 4 default profile templates (developer, researcher, architect, minimal)\n- UI design research synthesis document (13.5K words, 4-phase roadmap)\n\nAll tests passing, ready for CLI implementation (Task 1.4)", "session_duration_hours": 1.5, "resume_ready": true, "epic_1_completion_date": "2025-10-15", "git_commits": ["6190f85 - Epic 1 Task 1.4 CLI commands", "da01cfd - Epic 1 Tasks 1.1-1.3 foundation"], "lines_added_epic_1": "1,780+ lines (models, parser, detector, config generator, CLI)", "next_focus": "UI Phase 1: Event Bus + ADHD Theme System", "git_latest": "7c76391 - Merge with Claude Code Router + LiteLLM", "phase_1_week_1_goal": "Event bus operational, themes switchable, libtmux foundation", "architecture_analysis_complete": true, "deep_dives_total": 7, "decisions_logged": [37, 38, 39], "synthesis_updated": "docs/ARCHITECTURE-CONSOLIDATION-SYNTHESIS.md enhanced with Decisions #31-32", "total_container_savings": "-42% (19\u219211 containers)", "session_complete": true, "git_commits_this_session": ["2c18aec - Infrastructure consolidation", "b368ff9 - Zen MCP tracking + stdio fixes"], "decisions_ready_for_implementation": [31, 32], "next_session_action": "Restart Claude Code to activate Zen MCP, then use zen/planner to create ADHD-optimized implementation plan for 21-day consolidation roadmap", "zen_mcp_status": "Configured in .claude.json, requires Claude Code restart to activate", "files_committed": ["docker/mcp-servers/zen/zen-mcp-server/ (465 files, 91561 insertions)", ".gitignore (removed zen-mcp-server)"], "session_pause_reason": "Restart Claude Code to activate Zen MCP for infrastructure analysis", "restart_required_for": "Zen MCP tools (thinkdeep, planner, consensus, debug, codereview)", "current_task": "Infrastructure Consolidation Deep Analysis (Decisions #31-32)", "task_status": "PAUSED - Need Zen MCP for systematic risk analysis before execution", "next_action": "Switch to ui-build worktree for multi-instance orchestrator work", "infrastructure_analysis_plan": {"objective": "Systematically analyze infrastructure consolidation (Decisions #31-32) before ANY changes", "zen_tool": "zen/thinkdeep", "estimated_steps": 7, "analysis_focus": ["Mystery containers: dopemux-postgres-primary (5432) and dopemux-redis-primary - NOT in any compose file", "Active database dependencies: which services use which databases", "Data migration safety: what data exists, can we safely remove", "Execution sequence: optimal order to minimize downtime and risk", "Rollback strategies: how to undo if something breaks"]}, "discovered_state": {"postgres_containers": {"dopemux-postgres-age": {"port": 5455, "status": "ACTIVE (Up 2 hours, healthy)", "source": "docker/memory-stack/docker-compose.age.yml", "database": "dopemux_knowledge_graph (AGE extension)", "used_by": "ConPort MCP", "action": "KEEP - authoritative knowledge graph"}, "dopemux-postgres-primary": {"port": 5432, "status": "MYSTERY - running but NOT in any docker-compose.yml", "source": "UNKNOWN - needs investigation", "database": "UNKNOWN", "used_by": "UNKNOWN", "action": "INVESTIGATE BEFORE REMOVAL"}, "dopemux-postgres": {"source": "docker/memory-stack/docker-compose.yml (orphaned)", "database": "dopemux_memory", "status": "Defined but service disabled", "action": "Safe to remove compose definition"}, "conport-kg-postgres-age": {"source": "docker/conport-kg/docker-compose.yml", "status": "DEFERRED (never started)", "port_conflict": "5455 (conflicts with active postgres-age)", "action": "Safe to remove - never deployed"}}, "redis_containers": {"dopemux-redis-primary": {"status": "MYSTERY - running but NOT in any docker-compose.yml", "source": "UNKNOWN - needs investigation", "action": "INVESTIGATE BEFORE REMOVAL"}, "dopemux-redis-leantime": {"port": 6379, "status": "ACTIVE (PM plane)", "source": "docker/leantime/docker-compose.yml", "network": "leantime-net (isolated)", "action": "KEEP - PM plane authority boundary"}, "conport-kg-redis": {"source": "docker/conport-kg/docker-compose.yml", "status": "DEFERRED (never started)", "action": "Safe to remove - never deployed"}}, "vector_databases": {"milvus_stack": {"containers": ["milvus-etcd", "milvus-minio", "milvus-standalone"], "source": "docker/memory-stack/docker-compose.yml", "ports": ["9001:9001", "9000:9000", "19530:19530", "9091:9091"], "status": "RUNNING (needs verification)", "used_by": "claude-context MCP", "migration_target": "Qdrant (simpler, 1 container vs 3)"}, "qdrant": {"status": "ACTIVE (unhealthy - needs investigation)", "used_by": "dope-context MCP", "advantages": "Modern, single container, proven working"}}}, "critical_unknowns": ["How were dopemux-postgres-primary and dopemux-redis-primary started? (not in any compose file)", "What data do these mystery containers hold?", "Which MCP servers actively connect to them?", "Can we inspect their databases to see active usage?", "Is there another docker-compose file we haven't found?"], "consolidation_targets": {"phase_1_postgres": {"goal": "3 PostgreSQL \u2192 1 (dopemux-postgres-age only)", "safe_removals": ["dopemux-postgres (orphaned)", "conport-kg-postgres-age (DEFERRED)"], "requires_investigation": "dopemux-postgres-primary (mystery source)", "estimated_savings": "~1GB memory, 2 containers"}, "phase_2_redis": {"goal": "Redis consolidation to 2-3 instances", "keep": "dopemux-redis-leantime (PM plane isolation)", "requires_investigation": "dopemux-redis-primary (mystery source)", "target_architecture": "shared Redis + events Redis + Leantime Redis"}, "phase_3_vector": {"goal": "Milvus (3 containers) \u2192 Qdrant (1 container)", "migration_effort": "MEDIUM-HIGH", "risk": "Data migration, re-indexing time", "estimated_savings": "~1.5GB memory, 3 containers"}}, "zen_analysis_steps": {"step_1": "Evidence gathering: Find mystery container sources, inspect databases, check MCP configs", "step_2": "Dependency mapping: Which services depend on which databases (postgres-primary, redis-primary)", "step_3": "Data safety assessment: What data exists, is it needed, can we migrate/remove safely", "step_4": "Risk analysis: What breaks if we remove each container, rollback strategies", "step_5": "Execution planning: Optimal sequence, validation checkpoints, rollback procedures", "step_6": "Validation strategy: How to verify each phase succeeded, monitoring during execution", "step_7": "Final synthesis: Go/no-go decision, detailed execution runbook"}, "mcp_servers_to_check": ["ConPort MCP - which database? (likely postgres-age)", "dope-context - which vector DB? (likely Qdrant)", "claude-context - which vector DB? (likely Milvus)", "Serena - any database dependencies?", "GPT-Researcher - any database dependencies?"], "investigation_commands": {"find_compose_files": "find . -name 'docker-compose*.yml' -type f | grep -v node_modules", "inspect_postgres_primary": "docker exec dopemux-postgres-primary psql -U postgres -c '\\l'", "inspect_redis_primary": "docker exec dopemux-redis-primary redis-cli INFO", "check_mcp_connections": "grep -r DATABASE_URL docker/mcp-servers/ services/ --include='*.yml' --include='*.py'", "verify_milvus_usage": "docker ps | grep milvus && docker logs milvus-standalone --tail 50"}, "expected_total_savings": {"containers": "8 eliminated (2 PostgreSQL + 1 Redis + 3 Milvus + 2 DEFERRED)", "memory": "~2-3GB (PostgreSQL ~500MB each, Milvus stack ~1.5GB, Redis ~200MB)", "ports_freed": "5432, 9000, 9001, 19530, 9091 (if Milvus removed)", "maintenance_reduction": "Single PostgreSQL AGE, 2-3 Redis, 1 Qdrant vs current sprawl"}, "session_timestamp": "2025-10-16T07:15:00Z", "pause_safe": true, "context_preserved": true, "infrastructure_cleanup_session": {"zen_mcp_status": "\u2705 OPERATIONAL - Connected to Claude Code via stdio", "containers_removed": ["dopemux-postgres-primary (zombie from deleted unified.yml)"], "containers_formalized": ["dopemux-redis-primary (now managed by docker-compose)"], "volumes_cleaned": ["dopemux-mvp_postgres_primary_data", "dopemux_postgres_data", "dopemux_postgres_primary_data"], "storage_freed": "~1.5GB", "services_validated": ["ConPort \u2705 Redis connected", "redis-primary \u2705 healthy"], "decision_logged": "ConPort Decision #33"}, "decisions_this_session": [33, 34, 35], "files_modified": ["docker/mcp-servers/docker-compose.yml (-88 lines: removed unused services)", ".claude.json (+13 lines: Zen MCP stdio config)", "docker/mcp-servers/zen/zen-mcp-server/conf/cli_clients/ (+3 worktree configs)"], "architecture_validated": true, "proof_of_concept": "Created claude-main, claude-ui, claude-test CLI configs with working_dir set to respective worktrees", "restart_ready": true, "quick_resume": "ConPort has full context: Decisions #33-35, active_context updated, git committed. Restart Claude Code to activate Zen tools.", "accomplishments": ["Dope-context: Indexed 586 chunks (158 code + 428 docs), fixed 8 issues, AST chunking operational", "Worktree validation: All 3 MCP servers (Dope-Context, ConPort, Serena) fully worktree-aware with perfect isolation", "Zen-MCP: Fixed clink registry crash, 12 reasoning tools now available", "Tree-sitter upgraded 0.21\u21920.25.2 for AST-aware chunking", "Created OpenAI gpt-5-mini context generator ($0.05 per 50 files)", "3 git commits, 3 ConPort decisions, 2,100+ lines documentation"], "technical_notes": {"dope_context_status": "fully_operational", "collections": {"code_3ca12e07": "158 chunks", "docs_3ca12e07": "428 chunks"}, "ast_chunking": "working with tree-sitter 0.25.2", "context_generation": "gpt-5-mini ($0.05 per 50 files)", "search_performance": "<2s with 0.43-0.73 relevance", "cost": "$0.052 for initial 50 file index"}, "commits": ["4c19695 - dope-context validation", "2a4ed4f - worktree validation", "31c7e4b - zen-mcp fix"], "next_session": ["All MCP tools operational and validated", "Use dope-context search before implementing features", "Leverage worktree isolation for parallel development", "Use zen thinkdeep/planner/consensus for complex analysis"]}, "change_source": "update_active_context"}
./reports/conport_sqlite_exports/20260206T144006Z/quarantine__2026-02-04__SYSTEM_ARCHIVE__db_backups__context_20251024_181418_db/decisions.jsonl:9:{"id": 9, "timestamp": "2025-10-05T15:09:34+00:00", "summary": "Fixed statusline to display rich ADHD state from Engine (energy + attention)", "rationale": "Bug: statusline showed only boolean ADHD indicator instead of rich state. Root cause: metamcp_simple_query.py had hardcoded mock data and never queried the actual ADHD Engine. The Engine tracks comprehensive state (energy levels: very_low\u2192hyperfocus, attention: scattered\u2192hyperfocused) but this was lost at the integration boundary. Evidence-based diagnosis using Serena + Grep to locate both files and identify the missing connection.", "implementation_details": "Two-file fix: (1) scripts/metamcp_simple_query.py - Added _query_adhd_engine() method to query port 5448 health endpoint, extract energy_level and attention_state from current_state, graceful fallback to defaults if engine offline. (2) scripts/ui/metamcp_status.py - Added format_energy_level() with 5 states (\ud83d\udd34 VERY LOW, \ud83d\udfe0 LOW, \ud83d\udfe1 MED, \ud83d\udfe2 HIGH, \u26a1 HYPER) and format_attention_state() with 5 states (\ud83d\udcad SCAT, \ud83d\udd04 TRAN, \ud83c\udfaf FOCUS, \ud83d\udd25 HYPER, \ud83d\ude35 OVER). Updated generate_status_bar() to display both indicators. Tested: shows \ud83d\udfe1 MED | \ud83c\udfaf FOCUS with proper colors when engine offline (defaults), will show live state when engine running.", "tags": ["statusline", "adhd-engine", "bug-fix", "integration", "visual-feedback", "energy-tracking", "attention-tracking"]}
./reports/conport_sqlite_exports/20260206T144006Z/quarantine__2026-02-04__SYSTEM_ARCHIVE__db_backups__context_20251024_181418_db/decisions.jsonl:10:{"id": 10, "timestamp": "2025-10-05T15:21:19+00:00", "summary": "Replace MetaMCP broker with lightweight profile-based MCP management", "rationale": "Context window overload with 50+ tools from 8 MCPs was the original problem MetaMCP tried to solve. However, MetaMCP broker architecture is over-engineered for the problem. Modern solution: profile-based config files that reduce tools to 10-15 per use case (developer, researcher, architect). MCP protocol doesn't support lazy loading, so filtering must happen at config generation time. Profile approach is simpler, faster, and ADHD-friendly with auto-detection based on git branch, directory, ADHD state, and time of day.", "implementation_details": "3-phase rollout: Phase 1 (backward compatible) creates 'full' profile matching current 8-MCP setup as default. Phase 2 introduces developer/researcher/architect profiles for opt-in testing with 70% context reduction. Phase 3 enables smart auto-detection with confirmation prompts. Core components: (1) Profile YAML format with MCP list + ADHD config + auto-detection rules, (2) profile_manager.py for detection scoring (git 30%, directory 25%, ADHD 20%, time 15%, files 10%), (3) config_generator.py to transform profile -> Claude config.json, (4) ConPort integration for session save/restore during profile switches (7-10 sec). Implementation priorities: P0 (2 days) manual selection, P1 (1 week) auto-detect + switching, P2 (2 weeks) UI integration.", "tags": ["metamcp", "profile-manager", "context-management", "adhd-optimization", "mcp-selection", "config-generation", "architecture-decision"]}
./reports/conport_sqlite_exports/20260206T144006Z/quarantine__2026-02-04__SYSTEM_ARCHIVE__db_backups__context_20251024_181418_db/decisions.jsonl:12:{"id": 12, "timestamp": "2025-10-05T15:36:54+00:00", "summary": "Profile Manager Implementation Plan: 4 Epics, 14 Tasks, 58 Subtasks", "rationale": "Comprehensive breakdown created via Zen planner (6-step systematic analysis). Plan addresses MetaMCP replacement with lightweight profile-based MCP selection achieving 70% context reduction. Three-phase rollout (P0: manual selection, P1: auto-detection + switching, P2: UX polish) with parallel execution opportunities. Total timeline: 5-7 days single developer, 4-5 days with parallel team. Key innovations: weighted signal detection (git 30%, dir 25%, ADHD 20%, time 15%, files 10%), ADHD-friendly gentle suggestions (confidence thresholds), session preservation via ConPort, <10s profile switching target.", "implementation_details": "**4 Epics**:\n\nEpic 1 (P0 - 1.75 days): Profile Foundation\n- Task 1.1: YAML Schema (4h) \u2192 Pydantic models, parser, 4 default profiles\n- Task 1.2: Config Generator (5h) \u2192 Claude config.json generation with backup/rollback\n- Task 1.3: CLI Commands (3h) \u2192 dopemux start --profile, list, show, validate\n- Task 1.4: Testing (2h) \u2192 E2E tests, documentation\n- Deliverables: profile_manager.py, config_generator.py, cli.py, 4 YAML profiles\n\nEpic 2 (P1 - 1.5 days - PARALLEL with Epic 3): Auto-Detection\n- Task 2.1: Signal Collectors (6h) \u2192 Git (30%), Dir (25%), ADHD (20%), Time (15%), Files (10%)\n- Task 2.2: Scoring (4h) \u2192 Confidence calc, suggestion strategy (0.85/0.65/skip thresholds)\n- Task 2.3: CLI Integration (2h) \u2192 profile suggest, start --auto-detect\n- Deliverables: signal_collectors.py, scorer.py\n\nEpic 3 (P1 - 1.5 days - PARALLEL with Epic 2): Profile Switching\n- Task 3.1: ConPort Session (5h) \u2192 Save/restore session state (files, cursor, decisions)\n- Task 3.2: Claude Management (4h) \u2192 Process detection, SIGTERM/SIGKILL, restart\n- Task 3.3: Orchestration (3h) \u2192 dopemux switch <profile>, <10s optimization\n- Deliverables: session_manager.py, claude_manager.py, switcher.py\n\nEpic 4 (P2 - 2.5 days): UX Integration\n- Task 4.1: Statusline (3h) \u2192 Profile indicator [DEVELOPER] | MED | FOCUS\n- Task 4.2: Suggestions (4h) \u2192 Background detection, gentle prompts, quiet hours\n- Task 4.3: Management (3h) \u2192 create/edit/copy/delete/current commands\n- Task 4.4: Analytics (4h) \u2192 Usage tracking, stats dashboard, insights\n- Task 4.5: Migration (3h) \u2192 Pattern analysis, init wizard, documentation\n- Task 4.6: Documentation (3h) \u2192 User guide, CLI reference, dev docs\n- Deliverables: statusline_integration.py, suggestion_engine.py, analytics.py, migration.py + docs\n\n**Critical Path**: Epic 1 \u2192 (Epic 2 || Epic 3) \u2192 Epic 4 = 5.75 days minimum\n\n**Success Criteria**: 70% context reduction, <10s switch, >85% auto-detect accuracy, 100% backward compat\n\n**Risk Mitigation**: Early Claude config validation, backup/rollback always, parallelize operations, high confidence thresholds (0.85), graceful degradation\n\n**Files**: ~2,000 LOC production, ~1,000 LOC tests, 4 markdown docs\n\n**Continuation ID**: 467b312b-7f3b-4bef-806e-627f75f59189 (Zen planner session for plan updates)", "tags": ["profile-manager", "implementation-plan", "epic-breakdown", "zen-planner", "4-epics", "14-tasks", "58-subtasks", "parallel-execution", "adhd-optimized", "context-reduction", "auto-detection", "session-preservation", "5-7-day-timeline"]}
./reports/conport_sqlite_exports/20260206T144006Z/quarantine__2026-02-04__SYSTEM_ARCHIVE__db_backups__context_20251024_181418_db/decisions.jsonl:15:{"id": 15, "timestamp": "2025-10-05T15:59:20+00:00", "summary": "Adopt libtmux + Textual architecture with plugin system and ADHD-optimized themes", "rationale": "Comprehensive research on Python tmux applications reveals mature patterns that align perfectly with Decision #13 Hybrid TUI Architecture. Key validations: (1) libtmux provides ORM-style API for tmux entities (Server\u2192Session\u2192Window\u2192Pane), eliminating string parsing and enabling type safety; (2) Textual offers reactive UI patterns ideal for real-time task/log streaming dashboard; (3) Segment-based status bar architecture (like Powerline) matches existing metamcp_status.py design; (4) Plugin architecture with hook-based events enables extensibility without core modifications; (5) Theme inheritance system supports ADHD-specific color schemes (Nord, Dracula, Tokyo Night) with semantic colors for state (green=success, yellow=warning, red=error, purple=hyperfocus); (6) Session templates via YAML enable reproducible two-plane workspace layouts (PM plane + Cognitive plane); (7) fzf integration provides ADHD-friendly fuzzy search across sessions/windows/panes. Research confirms dopemux's unique value proposition: combining tmux multiplexing with ADHD accommodations (progressive disclosure, energy-aware layouts, break reminders, visual focus indicators) and two-plane architecture (Leantime for PM, ConPort for decisions) through Python's expressive power.", "implementation_details": "**Core Stack**: libtmux (tmux control) + Textual (TUI dashboard) + Rich (CLI output) + asyncio (responsiveness) + YAML+Jinja2 (config templates) + TPM-style plugin system. **Architecture Layers**: (1) DopemuxCore (libtmux.Server wrapper, event bus, plugin manager); (2) DopemuxSession (session lifecycle, two-plane layout management); (3) DopemuxTheme (256-color/true-color schemes with ADHD presets); (4) DopemuxPlugin (hook-based extensibility: on_session_created, on_pane_output, on_context_switch); (5) TextualDashboard (optional `dopemux tui` with Tree widget for sessions, PaneViewer for content, real-time updates via asyncio.create_task). **ADHD Enhancements**: (1) Adaptive layouts based on energy level (low=main-horizontal with large editor pane, high=tiled with multiple tasks); (2) Visual focus system using pane borders (active=#51afef bold, inactive=dim fg=colour240); (3) Break reminder integration in status bar (\ud83d\udfe2 <25min, \ud83d\udfe1 25-50min, \ud83d\udd34 >50min); (4) Smart pane management with auto-resize based on content importance; (5) Session persistence via tmux-resurrect pattern for interrupt recovery. **Two-Plane Templates**: YAML configs for common workflows: `dopemux start plan` (Leantime dashboard + Task-Master + ConPort query pane) vs `dopemux start code` (editor + tests + Serena LSP + logs). **Plugin System**: Python modules in ~/.config/dopemux/plugins/ with DopemuxPlugin base class, register_hooks() for event callbacks, access to dopemux API for tmux control. **Theme System**: JSON/YAML theme files with inheritance (base theme + overrides), automatic dark/light detection, semantic color roles (bg, fg, accent, warning, error, success, hyperfocus). **Performance**: Differential updates with pane content hashing, batch operations for multi-command tmux sequences, Redis caching for frequently accessed state, <50ms UI refresh target. **Distribution**: PyPI package `dopemux` with optional Docker image, extensive docs, example configs for common workflows.", "tags": ["ui-architecture", "libtmux", "textual", "research-synthesis", "plugin-system", "adhd-themes", "session-templates", "decision-13-enhancement", "implementation-ready"]}
./reports/conport_sqlite_exports/20260206T144006Z/quarantine__2026-02-04__SYSTEM_ARCHIVE__db_backups__context_20251024_181418_db/decisions.jsonl:30:{"id": 30, "timestamp": "2025-10-16T05:20:49+00:00", "summary": "MCP connectivity fix after multi-instance Docker cleanup", "rationale": "Multi-instance cleanup (commit 049d58c) removed MetaMCP broker infrastructure but left orphaned mode-specific configs (~/.claude/config/mcp_servers_*.json) pointing to non-existent proxy at localhost:12008. Additionally, ConPort Docker container wasn't connected to dopemux-network after recreation, causing database DNS resolution failures.", "implementation_details": "**Fixes Applied**: (1) Connected mcp-conport to dopemux-network manually (docker network connect). (2) Backed up and removed 5 orphaned mode configs (plan, act, research, quickfix, all) to ~/.claude/config/backup-20251015/. (3) Claude Code now uses ~/.claude/settings.json which has working stdio configurations for all MCPs. **Requires**: Restart Claude Code to pick up new configuration. **ConPort Status**: Now successfully connects to PostgreSQL (dopemux-postgres-age) and Redis. **Remaining Issues**: Zen MCP needs Python >=3.10 dependency fix, GPT-Researcher and Exa configurations in settings.json should work after restart.", "tags": ["mcp-fix", "multi-instance-cleanup", "network-configuration", "metamcp-removal", "conport-database"]}
./reports/conport_sqlite_exports/20260206T144006Z/quarantine__2026-02-04__SYSTEM_ARCHIVE__db_backups__context_20251024_181418_db/decisions.jsonl:35:{"id": 35, "timestamp": "2025-10-16T07:58:11+00:00", "summary": "Multi-Instance Architecture: Single Dopemux Orchestrator with Worktree-Aware CLI Spawning", "rationale": "**PROBLEM**: Current approach runs 3 separate dopemux instances (one per worktree), leading to:\n- Fragmented ConPort knowledge (each instance has own database connection)\n- Duplicate MCP server processes (Serena, ConPort stdio per instance)\n- No unified orchestration or cross-worktree awareness\n- 9 CLI processes with no coordination\n\n**USER REQUIREMENT**: \"1 dopemux spawning multiple CLI tools is the right approach. Unified knowledge but tagged per instance.\"\n\n**DISCOVERY**: Zen MCP's clink tool supports `working_dir` parameter (clink/models.py:48, clink/agents/base.py:116), enabling worktree-specific CLI spawning from single orchestrator.\n\n**ARCHITECTURE INSIGHT**:\nCurrent state (What's running NOW):\n- 3x `dopemux start` processes (main, worktree-test, ui-build)\n- Each spawns: Claude Code + Serena + ConPort\n- No communication between instances\n\nProposed state (Zen clink-enabled):\n- 1x dopemux orchestrator (main worktree)\n- Spawns CLI instances via clink with different working_dir\n- Unified ConPort knowledge graph with session_id tagging\n- Shared MCP services (Serena, dope-context, etc.)\n\n**KEY CAPABILITY UNLOCKED**:\n```json\n// conf/cli_clients/claude-ui.json\n{\n  \"working_dir\": \"/Users/hue/code/ui-build\",  // \u2190 Runs in ui-build worktree!\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nThen from main dopemux instance:\n```\nclink with claude-ui to build dashboard component  // Runs in ui-build worktree\nclink with claude-test to add integration tests     // Runs in test worktree\nclink with claude-main to implement auth           // Runs in main worktree\n```\n\n**COMPARISON TO OLD MULTI-INSTANCE DOCKER** (Decision #29 - removed):\n- OLD: MetaMCP broker with PORT_BASE offsets (3000, 3030, 3060)\n- OLD: Instance-specific container naming (CONTAINER_PREFIX)\n- OLD: Complex environment variable management\n- NEW: Simple working_dir in CLI config\n- NEW: Zen's clink handles orchestration\n- NEW: Native git worktree isolation (no Docker complexity)", "implementation_details": "**PROOF-OF-CONCEPT CREATED**:\n\nCreated 3 worktree-specific CLI configs in Zen:\n1. `conf/cli_clients/claude-main.json` \u2192 /Users/hue/code/dopemux-mvp\n2. `conf/cli_clients/claude-ui.json` \u2192 /Users/hue/code/ui-build  \n3. `conf/cli_clients/claude-test.json` \u2192 /Users/hue/code/dopemux-worktree-test\n\n**ARCHITECTURE DESIGN**:\n\n**Tier 1: Dopemux Orchestrator** (Single Instance)\n- Runs in main worktree: /Users/hue/code/dopemux-mvp\n- Provides: CLI coordination, ConPort access, shared MCP services\n- Entry point: `dopemux start` (no multi-instance detection needed)\n\n**Tier 2: Shared MCP Services** (Single Set)\n- ConPort MCP (stdio): Unified knowledge graph, session_id per CLI spawn\n- Serena v2 (stdio): Code navigation across all worktrees\n- dope-context (stdio): Semantic search across all worktrees  \n- Zen MCP (stdio): Orchestration engine with clink\n- Context7, GPT-Researcher, etc.: Shared by all CLI instances\n\n**Tier 3: Spawned CLI Instances** (Via Zen Clink)\n- `clink with claude-main` \u2192 Works in /dopemux-mvp\n- `clink with claude-ui` \u2192 Works in /ui-build\n- `clink with claude-test` \u2192 Works in /worktree-test\n- `clink with codex` \u2192 Can target any worktree\n- `clink with gemini` \u2192 Can target any worktree\n\n**ConPort Knowledge Graph Strategy**:\n\n**Unified Graph with Session Tagging**:\n```python\n# Each clink spawn gets unique session_id\nsession_id = f\"{cli_name}-{worktree_name}-{timestamp}\"\n\n# Active context tracks per-session\nactive_context = {\n  \"workspace_id\": \"/Users/hue/code/dopemux-mvp\",  # Always main repo\n  \"session_id\": \"claude-ui-20251016-0740\",\n  \"worktree_path\": \"/Users/hue/code/ui-build\",\n  \"branch\": \"ui-build\",\n  \"current_focus\": \"Dashboard component\"\n}\n\n# Shared knowledge (all sessions see):\n- Decisions (architectural choices apply to all worktrees)\n- System patterns (coding standards unified)\n- Cross-worktree progress (see what's happening everywhere)\n\n# Session-specific (isolated per CLI spawn):\n- current_focus (each CLI has own task)\n- session_start, session_duration\n- attention_state, energy_level\n```\n\n**IMPLEMENTATION PHASES**:\n\n**Phase 1: Enable Clink Worktree Support** (1-2 days)\n- \u2705 Create worktree-specific CLI configs (DONE)\n- \u2610 Restart Zen MCP to load configs\n- \u2610 Test basic clink spawning with working_dir\n- \u2610 Validate each CLI runs in correct worktree\n- \u2610 Confirm file operations respect working_dir\n\n**Phase 2: ConPort Session Management** (2-3 days)\n- \u2610 Update active_context schema: Add session_id, worktree_path, branch\n- \u2610 Modify ConPort MCP to accept session_id parameter\n- \u2610 Implement session tagging for all ConPort operations\n- \u2610 Add query filters: get_active_context(session_id=X)\n- \u2610 Dashboard shows all active sessions\n\n**Phase 3: Dopemux Orchestrator CLI** (3-4 days)\n- \u2610 `dopemux spawn claude-ui` \u2192 Wrapper for `clink with claude-ui`\n- \u2610 `dopemux spawn codex-main planner` \u2192 With role selection\n- \u2610 `dopemux sessions list` \u2192 Show all active clink sessions\n- \u2610 `dopemux sessions switch <id>` \u2192 Interactive session management\n- \u2610 Integration with dopemux UI (terminal dashboard)\n\n**Phase 4: Chat-Driven Development** (Future)\n- \u2610 `dopemux chat` \u2192 Zen chat tool as orchestrator\n- \u2610 Natural language: \"work on auth in main, ui in ui-build simultaneously\"\n- \u2610 Chat spawns appropriate clink instances automatically\n- \u2610 Coordinates multiple CLI agents for complex multi-worktree work\n\n**MIGRATION PATH** (From Current 3-Dopemux Setup):\n\n**Current State**:\n```bash\nTerminal 1: dopemux start  # in /dopemux-mvp\nTerminal 2: dopemux start  # in /ui-build  \nTerminal 3: dopemux start  # in /worktree-test\n```\n\n**Transition State** (Both work during migration):\n```bash\nTerminal 1: dopemux start  # Main orchestrator\n  > clink with claude-ui to build dashboard\n  > clink with claude-test to add tests\n\nTerminal 2/3: dopemux start  # Still available for heavy focused work\n```\n\n**Target State**:\n```bash\nSingle Terminal: dopemux start  # Orchestrates everything\n  > dopemux spawn claude-ui --task \"build dashboard\"\n  > dopemux spawn claude-test --task \"add integration tests\"  \n  > dopemux spawn codex-main planner --task \"plan auth migration\"\n  > dopemux sessions list  # See all active work\n```\n\n**ADHD BENEFITS**:\n- **Context Preservation**: Unified ConPort = no lost decisions across worktrees\n- **Reduced Cognitive Load**: Single entry point vs tracking 3 terminals\n- **Progressive Disclosure**: `dopemux sessions list` shows all work at glance\n- **Flexible Focus**: Spawn work in any worktree without leaving main session\n- **Parallel Work**: Multiple CLI instances run simultaneously, report back to orchestrator\n\n**TECHNICAL ADVANTAGES**:\n- Shared MCP services (1 Serena vs 3, 1 ConPort connection vs 3)\n- Unified knowledge graph (decisions visible across all work)\n- Better resource efficiency (fewer duplicate processes)\n- Simpler mental model (1 orchestrator vs N instances)\n\n**OPEN QUESTIONS** (Need Research/Testing):\n1. Can clink pass MCP server connections to spawned CLIs?\n2. How do spawned CLIs authenticate (inherit parent OAuth or separate)?\n3. Performance: Can 1 dopemux handle 3-5 concurrent clink spawns?\n4. Resource limits: Memory/CPU with multiple CLIs?\n5. Crash isolation: Does 1 failed clink spawn kill orchestrator?", "tags": ["multi-instance", "architecture", "clink", "worktrees", "orchestration", "conport-sessions", "adhd-optimization", "zen-mcp"]}
./reports/conport_sqlite_exports/20260206T144006Z/quarantine__2026-02-04__SYSTEM_ARCHIVE__db_backups__context_20251024_181418_db/decisions.jsonl:249:{"id": 249, "timestamp": "2025-10-24T05:17:02+00:00", "summary": "ConPort cleanup: 5 stale IN_PROGRESS items investigated and resolved via Zen thinkdeep", "rationale": "Systematically investigated 5 old IN_PROGRESS items (Oct 5-20) using Zen thinkdeep to determine actual status before marking done/blocked. Investigation revealed: 1 item genuinely blocked (#190 LiteLLM - waiting for database), 4 items completed but never marked (#141 TUI, #113 Serena migration, #30 Profile Foundation, #29 Architecture Consolidation). All items had clear evidence in codebase or ConPort decisions confirming status. Updates applied to clean ConPort memory.", "implementation_details": "**Investigation Results** (Zen thinkdeep, 6 steps, very high confidence):\n\n**#190 (Oct 20) - LiteLLM Database Setup**:\n- **Status**: BLOCKED \u2192 Waiting for PostgreSQL 'litellm' database creation\n- **Evidence**: Decision #210 describes requirement, no completion found\n- **Action**: Updated to BLOCKED with blocker reason\n\n**#141 (Oct 19) - Orchestrator TUI Day 1**:\n- **Status**: DONE \u2192 TUI implemented successfully\n- **Evidence**: Code exists in adaptive_layout.py (205 lines), tmux_metamcp_controller.py (325 lines)\n- **Action**: Marked as DONE with implementation reference\n\n**#113 (Oct 16) - Serena Migration**:\n- **Status**: DONE \u2192 Migration completed successfully\n- **Evidence**: CognitiveLoadManager in adhd_relationship_filter.py (805 lines)\n- **Action**: Marked as DONE with code reference\n\n**#30 (Oct 5) - Profile Foundation Task 1.2**:\n- **Status**: DONE \u2192 Epic 1 fully complete\n- **Evidence**: Decision #28 (Oct 15) states \"Epic 1 Profile Manager MVP Complete\" - all 4 tasks\n- **Action**: Marked as DONE with Decision #28 reference\n\n**#29 (Oct 5) - Architecture Consolidation**:\n- **Status**: DONE \u2192 All 6 deep dives completed\n- **Evidence**: Decisions #3-11 document all deep dives and synthesis\n- **Action**: Marked as DONE with Decision references\n\n**Summary**: 80% of stale items (4/5) were actually completed but never marked. Only 20% (1/5) genuinely blocked. ConPort memory now accurate.\n\n**Investigation Method**: Zen thinkdeep systematic analysis with codebase search, ConPort decision cross-referencing, and git history review. Confidence: Very High (0.95).", "tags": ["conport-cleanup", "stale-items-resolved", "zen-thinkdeep-investigation", "progress-accuracy"]}
